I work right down the street on Halsted, so this Starbucks is really convenient. However, I have noticed that my cups are never filled to capacity and I have had to ask the baristas to fill my drink to the rim (even with Americanos). Starbucks is not cheap and their prices continue to rise, so IF I decide to buy coffee there, I expect a full drink. If I wanted a tall, I would have ordered a tall. But my grande drinks are always filled to about (maybe a tad bit over) tall capacity. It may seem like a minor issue, but I am looking to get what I pay for and with Starbucks, especially this location, that has proven to be difficult. I have started drinking coffee more locally in recent years with an occasional trip to Starbucks out of sheer convenience, but these experiences with half-filled coffee cups for full coffee cup prices are just enough for me to officially end my relationship with Starbucks.

I used to come here all the time and always had quick and pleasant experiences, but now I go out of my way to a further Starbucks. Something changed this past year with the staff or management - drinks take at least 10 minutes to make (on a slow day), more than half of the time they have their mobile ordering turned off and my usual go-to's (Peppermint Mocha, Salted Caramel Mocha, Double Smoke Bacon Sandwich, Everything Bantan Bagels - simple stuff) are always unavailable. Last time I was there, they had mobile ordering turned off and 3 separate customers came in waiting for mobile orders that they did not receive. I waited 20 minutes for my drink that I ordered in store because they had to fulfill other mobile orders (which I originally tried to place), and the staff all seemed new so it took triple the time. The manager who was on duty was there did not assist with making one drink. Disappointed with the service here to say the least.

I’m frustrated because I stopped by 15 minutes ago at 7:15pm and the door was locked. There was a barista changing a trashcan in the vestibule who told me they’re closed? Online, both on the google app and on the starbucks website, the closing time is listed at 7:30pm. There are no hours listed on the store front so what was the disconnect? Did the baristas working close down early? Or have the hours changed and the website isn’t updated yet? The barista seemed to be trying to avoid me which was kinda fishy but who knows. I know $5 doesn’t make a difference, but hey, business is business! Probably won’t be coming back since I can’t count on the hours being consistent.
